review_blob: Beautiful dark-amber colored brew, sweet smell and even sweeter taste upon first hitting the palate.  The deScription of this beer mentions "caramel", and thats the first taste that comes to mind.  Aftertaste is more bitter, rounding out the flavor nicely.  Reminds me of some brews I enjoyed in Germany, fitting since its an Octoberfest-labelled beer.  Yet another solid offering from Samuel Adams.

My first pumpkin beer, but not my first Blue Moon product.  Rather pleasant surprise.  Pours a nice reddish-orange.  Probably the most pleasant smelling beer Ive rated yet, with pumpkin and spices including nutmeg, as well as gingerbread and cloves.  The spice flavor definately overpowers the pumpkin flavor, which is rather subtle.  A nice, quaint beer for a cool autumn day.
beer_name: Blue Moon Harvest Moon Pumpkin Ale

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Amber bodied, frothy white headed, flavorful malts with a nice finish.  Good for an American macrobrew...more hops than the "normal commercial" beers, Id put it beside some Samuel Adams brews because of that. Bottle says "brewed in Chippewa Falls, Wisconsin by 73 people who care." Well thanks, guys.

"Skunky" was probably coined to describe this beer.  By itself, Im convinced that its undrinkable, garnished with a lime its perhaps tolerable, and I think this is the only reason anyone drinks it, along with the "feel good summer" advertising campaigns.  I think that when properly garnished it does go down smoothly enough, and the finish lingers.  But this beer never fails to give me one helluva hangover, almost like they use some dirty south-of-the-border drinking water in the brewing process.  Personally I go with Pacifico over this beer.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)

review_blob: Beer is a smooth drinker, if you like Blue Moon Belgian Wheat as a treat every now and again, then this would be its everyday counterpart.  Wheat, honey, and slight taste of orange are all present, but not in excess.  Goes down easy and is very satisfying for the season in which it was intended.  One of my favorite summertime "any day" beers.
beer_name: Blue Moon Honey Moon Summer Ale

review_blob: One of my favorite "on tap and easy to find" bar beers.  Cloudy and creamy with a slight taste of citrus and spice.  Yes, garnish it with an orange, as these tastes will then be dramatically accented.  Goes down easy and is quite satisfying, even if it isnt a "true" Belgian...rather, is "Belgian-Style".

Very strong, sweet bing cherry taste, almost completely covers the wheat.  Aftertaste is tart, which I feel offsets the sweetness nicely.  Not a beer that you want to drink every day, but I find it especially refreshing as a treat from time to time.  Honestly somewhat surprised at some of the low scores, as this one is a very drinkable treat.

Smells good, hits the palate immediately with bitter hops and perhaps a slightly acidic flavor.  Balanced well though with some sweet undertones including the taste of caramel.  Very refreshing for a domestic, Id have to say that itd be my choice by far over the "typical" macrobrew Buds and Anheuisers.  A good "everyday" beer to drink between the microbrews.
